content.text: We added 2020 assessments based on XMLs, and later merged metrics for these new assessments to last year's assessments.
In 2019 assessments, numeric indicators have labels in their question text ex. "B1." which end in a newline character.
This is good. We should also add this newline character to the numeric questions in the new assessments
They also have the same newline characters in their response options ex. "B." which end in a newline character.
This is bad. Instead of a newline character, we should use a space ex. " ", and then merge the allowed values so there is one set for the metric.
Add newline character after the label in the question text of inner responses (numeric indicators) in the TSC 2020 assessments (maybe we should include this in the XML loader).
Remove the newline character after the label in the allowed values of all 2019 assessments, replace it with a space. Remove all duplicate allowed values which were added from 2020 assessments.

content.text: If a user clicks add more, they get taken into the search page. Once the user adds their assessments and clicks continue, they go to the identify your retailers page. If the user clicks back from the identify your retailers, they get taken to the “Find the right assessments page”.
